er understand our world and how we think about it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCognition. 0aEducationxPhilosophy. 0aKnowledge, Theory of. 4aEducation & History Of Education. 4aPhilosophy. 4aReligious Studies. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Mind & Body.2bisacsh  aphilosophical developments in epistemology, ways of learning, new thinking in education, problems with learning outcomes, John Henry Newman.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150175675740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501756757423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501756757.jpg  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK